        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>axonometric projection (technique) [300069662], parallel projection (technique) [300081303], projection (perspective and shading technique) [300053420], perspective and shading techniques [300053413], image-making processes and techniques [300053159], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a projection in which parallel lines project from the picture plane at an angle that is slanting or declining from the vertical or horizontal, as opposed to being perpendicular to the picture plane. It is distinct from "oblique perspective," in which parallel lines may appear to converge as they recede into space rather than remaining parallel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Proyección por el medio de que un objeto tridimensional que tenga en una de sus caras paralelas al plano del cuadro, es representada mediante la proyección de líneas paralelas que forman un ángulo con el plano del cuadro distinto a 90º.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar een projectie waarbij parallelle lijnen van het beeldvlak worden geprojecteerd met een hellende of terugwijkende hoek van de verticale of horizontale as, in plaats van loodrecht te staan op het projectievlak of het beeldvlak. Het begrip onderscheidt zich van 'schuin perspectief', waarbij de parallelle lijnen niet parallel lijken te blijven, maar lijken samen te komen wanneer ze in de ruimte verdwijnen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>平行投射線不垂直於投影面，而與垂直線或水平線成斜角的投影。與「傾斜透視」有所區隔，傾斜透視的投射線不完全平行，看起來像是往後方空間退縮，且最後將匯聚於一點。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
